=Because communication apprehension is context-specific and manifests differently across the four communication contexts #The lecture explained that McCroskey identified four communication contexts (public speaking, group discussions, meetings, dyadic) and that individuals can have different CA levels across these contexts. This is called "state CA"—anxiety triggered by specific situations. Someone might be perfectly comfortable in intimate one-on-one settings but terrified of speaking to large audiences.
~Because one-on-one conversations don't involve real communication #One-on-one conversations are a valid communication context (dyadic communication). The lecture specifically listed dyadic as one of McCroskey's four contexts.
~Because public speaking always causes anxiety for everyone #While many people experience CA during public speaking, it's not universal. 10-20% experience significant CA, but responses vary. The question is about why the same person can have different anxiety levels across contexts.
